  "updated_summary": "Under bright Oregon sunlight at the World Athletics Championships, Mutaz Essa BARSHIM, in a red and white striped singlet and gold-tinted sunglasses, achieved a perfect record with four clearances through 233, reaching 235m. His powerful run-up and clean Fosbury Flop over the bar, confirmed by the SEIKO scoreboard placing him first, elicited a massive roar from the crowd, with announcers praising his \"ridiculous\" performance. American athlete Shelby MCEWEN, in a red and blue singlet, faced a critical situation needing to clear 2.35m for second place after two misses at 233m, his personal best, but ultimately failed, walking away dejected as the scoreboard showed 'XX-' for his 2.33m attempt. The focus then shifted to South Korean athlete Sanghyeok WOO, in a white 'KOREA' tank top, who, after a focused preparation involving a scream and side steps, executed a clean Fosbury Flop over 2.33m, prompting excited commentary about his jump to 2.35m. WOO celebrated jubilantly, raising his arms, shouting, and running around the track, moving from fourth to second place. The stadium, alive with cheering fans and a visible South Korean fan group, saw the scoreboard confirm Woo's successful 2.33m jump, tying him for second. Later, WOO celebrated an incredible 2.35m jump, matching his outdoor personal best and country's outdoor record, placing him tied for first with BARSHIM. Italian athlete Gianmarco TAMBERI, an Olympic gold medalist, celebrated his successful 2.33m jump, placing him third, with commentators recalling his shared Tokyo gold with BARSHIM as a remarkable act of sportsmanship. The vibrant stadium, with visible 'OREGON 22' banners, cheering fans, and an American flag, featured strong shadows and lens flares, while a SEIKO scoreboard in the background briefly displayed 'TRIPLE JUMP W FINAL'."
